# API (NestJS Backend) Rules

## Architecture
- NestJS framework with GraphQL API
- Prisma ORM for database operations
- Row Level Security (RLS) implementation
- Clerk authentication integration

## Development Commands
```bash
pnpm dev         # Start development server
pnpm build       # Build the application
pnpm lint        # Lint the code
pnpm check:types # Type check
pnpm test        # Run unit tests
```

## Database & Prisma
- Use Prisma for all database operations
- Follow RLS patterns for data security
- Run migrations with `pnpm db:migrate`
- Generate Prisma client after schema changes
- Use proper transaction patterns for data integrity

## GraphQL
- Schema-first approach
- Auto-generated schema in `schema.graphql`
- Use code-first decorators
- Implement proper resolvers with authentication
- Use DataLoader for N+1 query prevention

## Authentication
- Clerk integration for user management
- Use guards for route protection
- Implement proper authorization checks
- Use decorators for user context

## Testing
- Unit tests with Vitest
- E2E tests for API endpoints
- Mock external services in tests
- Maintain high test coverage

## File Structure
- Organize by domain modules
- Use proper NestJS module structure
- Separate DTOs, services, and resolvers
- Keep utilities in shared folders

## Error Handling
- Use NestJS exception filters
- Proper error responses
- Log errors appropriately
- Handle validation errors

## Performance
- Use caching where appropriate
- Optimize database queries
- Implement proper pagination
- Use proper indexing strategies